## What I found
This draft was already unusually clean — it had been through creator, fresh-eyes, and second-pass edits. Every mechanical check was green before I touched it: **0 em-dashes, 0 contrast pairs, 0 banned phrases**, description at 160 chars. So this was a light, surgical polish, not a rework.

## What I fixed (two edits)
1. **Stacked type-generalization openers.** "The Director Hiding Inside the Clown" was carrying two abstraction-led paragraphs back to back ("For a Four…" and "Fours reach for exactly that kind of discipline…") — the sentence-shape fingerprint the fresh-eyes note flagged and the DISTRIBUTION LEDGER meant to avoid. Re-anchored the second one to him: *"He had that kind of discipline in excess."*
2. **Verbal echo in the paradox beat.** The meme-section paragraph opened on "barely a disguise" and closed on "barely disguised at all." Replaced the close with *"The bit and the man were wearing the same clothes."* — lands the same paradox without the repeat, and no "thought X, was really Y" contrast engine sneaks back in.

I left line 119's "look at you without ever seeing you / the louder the costume…" pair alone — the second clause adds a dose-response escalation, so it's rhetorical emphasis with a new dimension, not pure restatement.

